06/09/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The 9th anniversary of the death of Mother Teresa was commemorated in her hometown of Skopje on Tuesday (5 September), at the Macedonian Academy of Sciences and Art. Born Agnes Gonxhe Bojaxhiu to an ethnic Albanian family on 27 August 1910, Mother Teresa devoted her life to helping the sick and the poor. She won the 1979 Nobel Peace Prize for her humanitarian activities around the world. She died in Calcutta on 5 September 1997. (A1 TV, MRT - 05/09/06)
